Document: MeshInstance2D  
Path: godot/classes/class_meshinstance2d.rst  
Summary: A 2D node for rendering meshes, offering performance benefits over Sprite2D for large transparent areas.  

Node used for displaying a Mesh in 2D. This can be faster to render compared to displaying a Sprite2D node with large transparent areas, especially if the node takes up a lot of space on screen at high viewport resolutions. This is because using a mesh designed to fit the sprite's opaque areas will reduce GPU fill rate utilization (at the cost of increased vertex processing utilization).  

Note: A MeshInstance2D can be created from an existing Sprite2D via a tool in the editor toolbar. Select the Sprite2D node, then choose Sprite2D > Convert to MeshInstance2D at the top of the 2D editor viewport.  

Tip: When a Mesh has to be instantiated more than thousands of times close to each other, consider using a MultiMesh in a MultiMeshInstance2D instead.
